The paper presents a proof system for evaluating arithmetic circuits and has applications in complexity theory, cryptography, and combinatorics. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC), cryptography and security (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and information theory (cs.IT).
